      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2023 R2) operates under documented QMS with version control, regression test suite, and traceable release notes.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2023 R2 is a commercially validated solver maintained under ISO 9001-certified QMS. DePuy Synthes internal SOP QA-FEA-003 mandates version locking and regression testing prior to production use. Required and achieved level both Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions demonstrate solver correctness for linear elastic structural analysis.",
      "rationale": "Patch test and cantilever beam benchmark cases confirm correct implementation of solid and contact elements relevant to the pedicle screw model. Results match analytical solutions within 0.1%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between successive refinement levels; Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate asymptotic solution.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh convergence study (coarse/medium/fine, element edge lengths 0.8/0.5/0.3 mm at critical fillet) shows stiffness QoI convergence of 1.4% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI < 1.8%. Production mesh uses fine level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; contact status monitored for oscillation.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used for linear elastic phase; iterative PCG with residual tolerance 1e-8 for nonlinear contact iterations. No contact status oscillation observed across 47 load increments. Force residual norm < 1e-6 at convergence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts completed prior to submission.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by a second analyst not involved in original construction per SOP QA-FEA-003 §4.2. Boundary condition application, contact pair definitions, and QoI extraction scripts independently verified. No errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear elastic model with frictional contact is appropriate for the loading regime; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 static compression-bending operates below yield for stiffness QoI. Linear elastic continuum model with von Mises plasticity for yield force prediction is established in peer-reviewed literature (Nagaraja et al. 2019). Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod interface validated in prior published work."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometry inputs traceable to measured lot-specific data; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of production screws and rods (lot 2025-A). Material properties sourced from internal dataset MAT-2025-0047 (Ti-6Al-4V ELI and UHMWPE). Input uncertainty propagated via one-at-a-time sensitivity study; combined input uncertainty contribution to stiffness QoI estimated at ±2.1%. Dataset vintage (2025-09-12) predates the November 2025 model revision; engineering assessment concluded alloy lot was unchanged and the revision (fillet mesh refinement) did not alter material input requirements, so re-characterization was judged unnecessary."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production-representative hardware; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to nominal geometry.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated screws and 5.5 mm Ti rods. Dimensional inspection of all screws and rods via CMM; all within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Two-laboratory split (6+5) provides inter-laboratory reproducibility data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of conditions in the COU or sensitivity to condition variation is demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single test condition (6° offset block angle, 44 mm intervertebral body height per ASTM F1717 Table 1). Sensitivity to block angle variation not characterized experimentally. Achieved level below required; this gap is noted and accepted given that the standard mandates the single geometry and the model is not used to extrapolate beyond this condition."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters match experimental specimen parameters within measurement uncertainty; equivalency formally documented.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry parameterized from CMM measurements of the tested constructs. Material properties assigned from lot-matched coupon data. Torque-preload conversion for screw seating verified against torque-angle records from assembly. Equivalency table cross-referencing model inputs to test records completed in technical report TR-COU1-2025."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for each QoI; all values below 1.96 threshold.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 §6.4 for stiffness (1.31), yield force (1.54), and force at 40 mm (1.72). All three below the pre-established threshold of 1.96. Percentage differences also below 10% bound. Graphical overlay of FEA and experimental load-displacement curves included in TR-COU1-2025 Figure 7."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the regulatory submission claims and clinical performance requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary regulatory QoIs for ASTM F1717 spinal implant submissions. Force at 40 mm displacement is a secondary QoI required by FDA guidance. All three QoIs are directly predicted by the FEA model and compared to experimental measurements, establishing direct relevance to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) is the same scenario as the COU; no extrapolation required.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity is co-incident with the COU: the same loading mode (static compression-bending), the same construct geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, 5.5 mm rod), and the same test standard (ASTM F1717) are used in both validation and the intended regulatory submission. No extrapolation in loading mode, geometry, or material is required."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap is accepted because ASTM F1717 specifies a single test geometry and the model is not used to extrapolate beyond that geometry. The three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) each satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%. The assessment team noted that both input datasets carry a dataVintage predating the November 2025 model revision (mesh refinement at rod-screw fillet) by four to eight weeks; the team concluded in engineering assessment that the revision was not material to the datasets' relevance and deferred formal re-validation to the next annual review. On balance, the credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the intended regulatory use.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
